## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of up-to-date data and the inherent complexity of measuring the direct impact of carbon credits on global emissions. Additionally, the effectiveness of carbon credits can vary significantly depending on the regulatory framework and market conditions in different regions. Further empirical research and longitudinal studies are needed to comprehensively evaluate the long-term impact of carbon credits on emission reductions.